intro:
Thank you for participating again! 

In this study, we will ask you once again to provide ratings of several jokes, cartoons, and videos.

 
Information about the study 

 

This study is being conducted by the Department of Social Psychology at Tilburg University. The intention of this study is to research and gain knowledge on how people rate humorous content. This study will take approximately 10-15 minutes to complete.

 

Participation, Benefits and Risks 

Participation in this research study is completely voluntary. You have the right to withdraw at any time or refuse to participate entirely without providing any explanation. If you desire to withdraw, please simply close your internet browser. There will be no negative consequences if you withdraw or refuse to participate. Risks are minimal for involvement in this study. It is very unlikely that participating in this study would affects you in a negative way emotionally or otherwise. The content of the study was screened beforehand to ensure that no offensive or unpleasant content is featured. 



Requirements

To participate in this study, you need to be at least 18 years old. 



Confidentiality 

All data obtained from participants will be kept anonymous. There will be no record that links the data collected from you with any personal data from which you could be identified (e.g.,your name, address, email, etc.). The anonymous data may be made available to researchers via accessible data repositories and possibly used for novel purposes. The data will be stored for at least 10 years. If you have questions regarding this study, you may contact the researcher Hannes Rosenbusch at h.rosenbusch@tilburguniversity.edu. This study has received approval from the Tilburg School of Behavioral Sciences’ Ethical Review Board. If you have any remarks or complaints regarding this research, you may also contact the Ethics Review Board of Tilburg School of Social and Behavioral Sciences via erb@tilburguniversity.edu. 



Thank you for taking the time to participate in this study!
